events.name: Cloud study jam Day '18 Tororo
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?

Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

events.name: DevFest Tororo 2018
events.description:
We are excited to announce our DEVFEST 2018 happening on 9th February at Hotel Classic - Tororo.

We will be focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies to empower our developer community in Eastern Uganda. We will have proven tech gurus and tech enthusiast speakers who will deliberate and highlight on how to be better developers not forgetting learning how to code with Google technologies.

Join us on 24th November from 8:30 pm to 5:00 pm for experience speaker sessions, codelabs and a design sprint.

Requirements:

- Those who would like to get their hands dirty with code are advised to carry a laptop.

- RSVP the event on Meetup.
events.how_to_find_us: Tororo Rock Hotel is 10 kms from the border on the main Kampala-Kenya Rd.
